    "description": "&quot;A tendency toward the abstract is inherent in linear expression: graphic imagery being confined to outlines has a fairy-like quality and at the same time can achieve great precision.&quot;\n– Paul Klee (1920)\n\n&quot;For the present at least, I shall restrict my work to the ordinary world of the senses, since that is the world in which we still live. But nevertheless art even now form a transition to the finer regions, which perhaps I am incorrect in calling spiritual, for everything that has form is not yet spiritual, as I read somewhere. But it is nonetheless the path of ascension away from matter.&quot;\n– Piet Mondriaan, Summer of 1909\n\n&quot;Art today is moving in directions of which our forebears had no inkling; the Horsemen of the Apocalypse are heard galloping through the air... – new artists are signaling to one another from all sides; a glance, a touch of the hand, is enough to convey understanding.&quot;\n– Franz Marc, 1912.",
